[size=5]Features[/size]
[list]
[*] Universally replaces the default crosshair with a round dot.
[*] Use [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/4017]Gears[/url] & [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/2409/]Quartz[/url] to:
[list]
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640?tab=videos#lg=2&slide=2]Customize the crosshair with Fallout 4's signature green color[/url].
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640?tab=videos#lg=2&slide=1]Change the crosshair shape to a round or square dot[/url].
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640?tab=videos#lg=2&slide=0]Use the vanilla crosshair when holding ranged weapons[/url].
[*] Use [url=https://www.color-hex.com/]https://www.color-hex.com/[/url] to generate your RGBA color.
[*] The mod fallbacks to default game values if you are not using Gears: Round white dot with 75% transparency.[/list]
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5601]Immersive Crosshair[/url] and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640]Dot Crosshair[/url] mods are designed to complement each other.
[list]
[*] Hides crosshair when not having an interactable. 
[*] Hides crosshair when using weapons with iron sights.[/list]
[*] Compatibility: this mod is compatible with other mods that hide the crosshair. For example use [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/3252]Danzo No Crosshair[/url] instead of Immersive Crosshair in order to have a round dot always visible except when in aiming mode.
[*] Game Version: 1.0. Install with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/about/vortex/]Vortex[/url].
[/list]
